# moveit-cl0p-analysis-playbook

This repo is a defensive, educational analysis of the CL0P / MOVEit incident. It contains notebooks demonstrating static analysis on benign data, detection rule templates, and notes for responders. No malware or exploit code is included.

![Safety](https://img.shields.io/badge/Samples-Benign%20Only-green) ![Purpose](https://img.shields.io/badge/Purpose-Defensive%20Education-blue)

unzip moveit-cl0p-analysis-playbook.zip
cd moveit-cl0p-analysis-playbook
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Add benign static-analysis playbook: strings, entropy, Sigma/YARA, notes"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/moveit-cl0p-analysis-playbook.git
git push -u origin main

README.md
/notes                # markdown writeups
  ├─ 01-overview.md        # high-level timeline of the incident (sources cited)
  ├─ 02-attack-chain.md    # TTPs, killchain, where the webshell fits
  └─ 03-detection.md       # recommended detections
/notebooks            # Jupyter notebooks (static analysis helpers, visualizations)
  └─ pe_strings_and_entropy.ipynb
/rules                # detection signatures
  ├─ sigma/
  │   └─ moveit_webshell_sigma.yml
  └─ yara/
      └─ sample_strings.yar
/scripts              # safe parsing + tooling (benign)
  ├─ parse_iocs.py         # parse public IOCs (no malware)
  └─ pe_summary.py         # parse PE headers of benign samples & calculate entropy
/data                 # small, benign sample files or synthetic examples only
  └─ benign_samples/     
docs/                 # exported PDFs, diagrams
